cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.IT

The paper proposes a solution to the problem of universal representation of graphs using neural networks, specifically message-passing neural networks. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the usefulness of the proposed solution in the field of communications, which could potentially fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the case study presented in the paper involves delay prediction in queuing networks, which could be considered as information theory (cs.IT).
